	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Apr 8th 1:15 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60753><span id= >Soop</span></a><br><span id=notbold>110 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.12]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Yeah, it only holds small or tiny itmes but there are more small items than you might realize.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have had one of these on my monk for a long time and really like it.  In addition to food and bandages, I keep anything that weighs more than .1 in it that fits... when full, I start moving stuff to my ralic pack by weight, lighter stuff first.<br>I started me a monk on a new server and farmed spiderling silks for pp. (lots of tradespeople on that server).  I quickly (in under 4 days played) made about 10k pp off the silks and one of the first purchases was this bag for my new monk.  I gave all my stuff there away soon after starting there though.<br><br>Moral of the story, this bag is not hum-drum.  It is a sweet piece of gear that is well worth investing time or pp in.  especially if you play a monk or cleric (heavy armor and weak str).</p>&nbsp;<br>Soop 49ish War- Castouts<br>Brell<br><br>Pugette Tripsalott<br>54 Monk - Castouts - Brell<br><br>Raynn Fahling<br>54 Druid - Castouts - Brell</td></td></tr>
